## Context

- cytokine-network-flare-prediction: Project in 'analysis' status. Completed full interpretation of all 5 analyst tasks.
- Meta-analysis: 12 studies, 132 records, 8/10 analytes analyzed. ALL 8 significant. IL-1β largest effect (g=1.52), IL-6 second (g=1.46). I²=0% across all. IL-10 only downregulated (g=-0.82). LOO robust.
- Network: 22 nodes, 34 edges. IL-6 hub confirmed (11 outgoing edges). NLRP3→IL-1β independent arm correct. CIRS/BBB modules structurally present but unmeasured (10/22 nodes grey). IFNγ epigenetic persistence node present.
- Axis: Innate dominant (1.36), Th1 (1.10), Th17 (1.05), Regulatory suppressed (-0.82), Th2 unmeasured (0.0). Distinguishable from general infection by regulatory suppression pattern.
- Prediction: AUC=1.0 for both models — artifact of study-level aggregate classification, NOT clinical utility. Needs individual patient data.
- Treatment response: All 5 treatments produce IDENTICAL results — pipeline falls back to full dataset when no treatment annotations found. Methodological limitation, not biology.
- Journal entries: #1874 (meta-analysis), #1875 (network), #1876 (axis classification), #1877 (prediction critique), #1879 (treatment response critique)
- Tasks created: #1228 (developer — add treatment annotation support), #1229 (research_director — review comprehensive findings and limitations)
- Critical blind spots: (1) Th2 cytokines (IL-4, IL-13) unmeasured, (2) individual patient-level data needed for meaningful prediction, (3) treatment-specific cytokine data absent, (4) CSF data absent, (5) 10/22 network nodes unmeasured
- Next: Await research_director review (#1229). Developer to add treatment annotations (#1228). Seek IPD from ImmPort/GEO/authors. CSF data for BBB validation.
